  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/4504370/" class="title-link">百转千回的一段二战故事</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-4504370"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/block/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img1.doubanio.com/icon/u2776432-149.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/block/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">D.B</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar40 main-title-rating" title="推荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2010-12-05"
      class="main-meta">2010-12-05 22:13:38</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_4504370_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  我不热衷任何形式战争题材的电影或书籍甚至历史，因为战争背景下的人性是狭隘和扭曲的。这种人性对人类精神世界的进化也无任何益处。可是当人被迫被卷入战争的漩涡后，在激烈冲突的撞击下如何反应，坚持和生存的话题，我却很希望了解。 Unbroken还原的就是一个二战为背景下，一...

                    <a class="pl" href="https://book.douban.com/review/4504370/#comments">(14回应)</a>
                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">29有用 / 3没用</span>
                        <span class="publisher left">
                            Random House2010版</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="review_4504370_full" class="hidden">
            <div id="review_4504370_full_content" class="full-content"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
